---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy — JSONKit';
const description =
  'How JSONKit handles your data: what we collect, what we do not collect, third-party services we use, and your rights.';

const lastUpdated = 'April 30, 2026';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-balance text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-5xl dark:text-white">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="article">
      <h2>1. Summary</h2>
      <p>
        JSONKit is a static website that runs JSON-related utilities entirely inside your browser. We do not
        operate a backend that processes your JSON, we do not require accounts, and we do not log your inputs.
        This page explains the small set of things we <em>do</em> collect, who else may collect data through this
        site, and what choices you have.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Data you provide to the tools</h2>
      <p>
        Every tool on this site (Formatter, Validator, Minifier, Converters, Diff, JSONPath Query, etc.) runs
        100% client-side. The JSON you paste is parsed and processed in your browser by JavaScript loaded from
        our static files. <strong>Your input is never transmitted to our servers</strong> because there are no
        servers in the processing path — JSONKit is hosted as static assets on a content delivery network.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Data we collect automatically</h2>
      <h3>3.1 Web analytics</h3>
      <p>
        We use a privacy-respecting analytics provider (Vercel Web Analytics) to count page views and understand
        which tools are popular. The provider does not set advertising cookies, does not build cross-site
        profiles, and the data we see is aggregated and anonymized.
      </p>
      <h3>3.2 Server logs</h3>
      <p>
        Our hosting provider (Vercel) keeps short-lived request logs that include IP addresses, timestamps, and
        URLs requested. These logs are used to detect abuse and operate the service. We do not associate them
        with your inputs and we do not sell or share them.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies and local storage</h2>
      <p>JSONKit uses the following only:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Local storage</strong> — to remember your theme preference (light/dark) on this device. This
          never leaves your browser.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics cookie</strong> — set by our analytics provider for de-duplication of page views.
          See the provider's documentation for details.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>JSONKit does not use third-party tracking pixels or social media trackers.</p>

      <h2>5. Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        JSONKit may display advertising provided by third-party networks such as Google AdSense in order to fund
        hosting, domain costs, and ongoing development. When ads are enabled, the ad network may set cookies and
        process limited information (such as IP address and user agent) to serve and measure ads. You can
        review and control personalized advertising at
        <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">adssettings.google.com</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not share any JSON content you process on this site with advertising networks. Ads are served
        based on the page's general topic, not based on the data you paste.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Third-party services</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — static hosting and edge delivery.</li>
        <li><strong>Vercel Web Analytics</strong> — aggregated, privacy-respecting page analytics.</li>
        <li><strong>Google AdSense</strong> — advertising (when enabled).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        JSONKit is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children. If
        you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us so we can remove it.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live (e.g. the EU/EEA, the UK, California), you may have rights to access,
        correct, delete, or restrict processing of your personal data, and to object to direct marketing. Since
        we do not maintain user accounts, most rights apply only to the limited data described above.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        Server access logs are typically retained for a few weeks by our hosting provider before being purged.
        Aggregated analytics are retained for as long as they remain useful for understanding site performance.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy when we change the tools we use or how we run the service. The "Last
        updated" date above reflects the most recent change. Material changes will be highlighted on the
        homepage for a reasonable time.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions, comments, or requests about this policy can be sent via the GitHub repository at
        <a href="https://github.com/blank-knight/jsonkit/issues" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
          github.com/blank-knight/jsonkit/issues
        </a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
